obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

obo:BFO_0000066  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_1265  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Rizzoli et al perform immunofluorescent staining of hippocampal neurons for SV marker protein synaptophysin I and syntaxin-6. The data demonstrates significant overlap in the signals for both proteins, which suggests presynaptic localization of syntaxin.-6. Supporting data for this finding is delivered by immunoblotting of fractions from rat brain subcellular fractionation (similar to Takamori et al 2006, Cell), which shows modest, however clear, enrichment of stx6 in SVs. Furthermore, immunoEM images with antibody against syntaxin 6 show that the protein is present on small vesicular membranes containing synaptic vesicle proteins.\nSyntaxin 6 forms a fusion complex with EE SNAREs vti1a, VAMP4 and syntaxin-13, see Brandhorst, D et al, PNAS, 2009, PMID: 16469845). The presence on a subset of purified SV supports the view that the protein is localized predominantly to presynaptic early endosomes involved in SV-recycling.\n\n12/2/2018 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Preparation of subcellular fractions\nSynaptic vesicles were prepared as described (21). Synaptosomes were\nprepared from adult rats by discontinuous Ficoll gradient centrifugation." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1265" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

